  "prompt": "Our startup has an exciting announcement to make about one of our first partnership deals and that company making an investment as well. Is there a checklist or step by step guide of \"to-dos\" for announcing?",
  "response": "Here's a comprehensive checklist for announcing a partnership and investment:\n\nPre-Announcement Preparation:\n1. Legal review\n- Review partnership agreement terms\n- Ensure all legal documentation is finalized\n- Get sign-off from both companies' legal teams\n\n2. Internal Alignment\n- Brief key leadership/executives\n- Prepare internal communication\n- Align messaging across teams\n- Coordinate spokesperson(s)\n\n3. Press/Communication Strategy\n- Draft press release\n- Prepare key messaging points\n- Determine announcement channels\n- Create boilerplate company descriptions\n- Plan social media posts\n\n4. Technical Logistics\n- Prepare company website updates\n- Ready logo/graphics\n- Create landing page/announcement section\n\n5. Announcement Distribution\n- Draft email to investors\n- Notify employees\n- Prepare investor/press relations materials\n- Create media list for press release distribution\n\n6. Post-Announcement Follow-up\n- Monitor media coverage\n- Respond to inquiries\n- Track social media engagement\n- Prepare leadership for potential interviews\n\n7. External Communication Channels\n- Press release\n- Company blog\n- LinkedIn announcement\n- Twitter/social media posts\n- Email newsletter\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific section of this checklist?",
